Hmm, I see... And then... Mm-hmm... Oh! Good to see you, %PLAYERNAME%!
I was totally absorbed in my investigation of a most curious phenomenon in the area. Maybe you’ve noticed it yourself?
You know—the large boulders all over and the pieces of rock that look like they were broken off?
Perhaps you can help put some fire to all the smoke. Would you mind canvassing the area and letting me know if you find anything noteworthy?
Aha! Looks like Bagon, the Rock Head Pokémon, is responsible for the recent rocky wreckage.
Bagon aspire to one day soar through the sky. As if trying to dispel their frustration over their inability to do so, they slam their hard heads against huge rocks, shattering them into pebbles.
In fact, there are some theories that suggest this head-bashing behavior stimulates cells that affect their evolution!
Fascinating, isn’t it? Let’s test the theories out and evolve a Bagon!
And what have we here, %PLAYERNAME%? Well, well, it’s Shelgon, the Endurance Pokémon! Excellent work.
Shelgon’s shell is iron-hard and repels enemy attacks. When it’s waiting to evolve, it often hides away in a cavern.
And while it’s shut up in its shell, I hear it still dreams of the day it’ll be able to fly.
Why don’t we give your Shelgon a helping hand to see what new heights—literally—it can reach?
Impressive! You helped Shelgon’s dreams come true!
Salamence are overjoyed that they can finally take wing. They fly all over the place and usually don’t land until they’re completely exhausted and need to sleep.
I must say, this does open up all kinds of questions about what else Dragon-type Pokémon are capable of. It’s really inspiring.
And while I don’t recommend you bang your head into rocks to make your dreams come true, I’m sure the sky’s the limit for you too, %PLAYERNAME%!
Hello there, %PLAYERNAME%! Have you happened to do any exploring today?
It’s quite the sight, let me tell you! It’s lousy with Bellsprout out there!
They tend to prefer hot and humid places, but right now they seem to be everywhere.
And you know, there’s still plenty for us to learn about the Flower Pokémon. Would you be a pal and catch one for us to study?
Welcome back, %PLAYERNAME%. And what a great specimen you’ve brought!
Did you know that despite their slender frames, they can move lightning fast to catch insects? One more reason to be glad we’re not bugs!
But there’s more for us to learn about this fascinating Pokémon! Drop by again after you’ve evolved your Bellsprout into Weepinbell.
I’ll leaf through my Weepinbell research notes so I’m ready for you when you get back!
Hey now, that’s got to be the Weepinbell of the ball! Let me take a closer look.
Aha! You see that large hook on its rear end? Weepinbell tend to use that to hook themselves on tree branches when they sleep.
In other words, if you see your Weepinbell yawning, find it a tree on the double!
But there’s no time for us to be snoozing. How about you evolve Weepinbell into a Victreebel and bring it back here?
Hey, you’re victree-orious! Vic-tree...riffic? Ahem. Let’s have a look at your Victreebell, %PLAYERNAME%.
These large, plant-like Pokémon live in huge colonies, deep within the jungle. No one who’s visited has returned to tell the tale. That’s sure foreboding!
Although if I put my professor cap on and think about it, how do we know about the colonies unless someone DID make it back?
There’s something to ponder! In the meantime, thanks for letting me observe your Victreebel. I’m sure you’ll be fast friends in no time—just watch out for that prey-dissolving acid!
Aha! I hoped we’d have a run-in today, %PLAYERNAME%!
I was out hiking earlier when I saw a quick flash of something in the trees—something unusual.
I can’t say for certain, but it may have been the Mythical Pokémon Zarude! Or possibly just some falling leaves.
Either way, would you keep an eye—or even two—out for any unusual Grass-type Pokémon while you’re exploring?
%PLAYERNAME%, just the person I wanted to see!
I managed to spot our elusive friend again, and I can confirm that it’s definitely a Pokémon!
Unfortunately, it zipped away before I could get a closer look. Why don’t you canvas the area?
In the meantime, I’ll put my nose to my notes and see if I can’t confirm its identity.
Excellent, you’re back! I’ve got fantastic news, %PLAYERNAME%!
After digging into my archives, I can confirm that this mystery Pokémon is indeed none other than the Mythical Pokémon Zarude!
They tend to move in packs, but I can’t be certain how many we’re dealing with. It doesn’t matter, though. Either way, we must approach carefully!
I’m going to dive back into research and uncover whatever I can about Zarude’s behavior to help you prepare for this encounter.
Welcome back, %PLAYERNAME%! I have some super interesting tidbits to share about our elusive friend, Zarude!
When the vines on its body are torn off, they enrich the soil, and cause plants to grow large and lush.
Interesting, right? And useful, too! Do be on the lookout for any unusually lush areas—that could indicate a Zarude is close by!
You take care of that and let me know what you find. I’ll take some more time to study up.
%PLAYERNAME%, thanks to your exemplary field work, we’ve managed to locate the exact location of our Zarude.
I don’t think I have to remind you to be careful—it’s incredibly aggressive, and other forest Pokémon fear it. But I’m sure a talented Trainer like you can earn its trust in no time.
Just treat it like any other Pokémon—approach with patience and an open heart. Then I’m sure you’ll have yourself a steadfast new companion!
Great work so far, and good luck with what’s to come!

Your decorated snapshot will be saved as a separate image. This will use up any stickers you applied.
To place a sticker, select it and then tap where you want it on the snapshot. Pinch the sticker to resize it. Tap the X to remove it.
Adjust stickers to suit your photo
You can use stickers to decorate the snapshots you take. Swipe up on the sticker panel at the bottom of the screen to select stickers.
Stickers placed on photos will be consumed once you save your picture. To return stickers to your inventory, tap "don't save" when prompted.
Hi, %PLAYERNAME%. I have some troubling news to share.
Team GO Rocket members have been popping up in greater numbers—and you and I both know that wherever those troublemakers are, chaos is sure to follow.
We need more info. Why don’t you go confront some of them and see what intel you can get your hands on?
The more we learn, the better prepared we’ll be to stop them—that’s the power of knowledge!
Those Team GO Rocket Grunts weren’t the chatty sort, were they, %PLAYERNAME%?
Not to worry! We’ll just cut right to the source and find where their rabble-rousing leaders are hiding!
But until we can track them down, keep seeking out Grunts and purify any Shadow Pokémon you come across. Rescuing them from those rascals is a top priority.
I know a Trainer like you is more than up to the task!
Great work out there, %PLAYERNAME%! I wish I could say I did as well with my own search here.
Sadly, I haven’t been able to track down Team GO Rocket’s leaders—Arlo, Cliff, and Sierra. Not to worry, though! Any professor worth their salt always has a plan B!
If you can collect some Mysterious Components, we’ll be able to knock together a Rocket Radar!
With top-tier tech like that in our hands, there’s no way those miscreants will be able to hide from us.
Amazing work, %PLAYERNAME%! You really gave those Team GO Rocket leaders what for!
That said, even putting their leaders out of commission hasn’t put a stop to Team GO Rocket’s activity. Which means we’ll need to escalate our little issue all the way to the top—to Giovanni.
Be careful, though. He’s more powerful than any other member of Team GO Rocket. But if there’s anyone who can put him in his place, it’s you.
Kudos to you, %PLAYERNAME%! You showed Giovanni and his band of bullies and malcontents that they aren’t welcome around here!
...For now, at least. There’s not a doubt in my mind that those louts will be back eventually. But at least for now, the Pokémon in this area are safe, and we have you to thank.
A victory like this calls for a celebration—perhaps a nice bowl of Pinap Berries?
And know I speak from the heart when I say this: thank you for keeping the Pokémon of our world safe. Now go and enjoy some well-earned rest!
%PLAYERNAME%! Just who I was looking for!
We’re getting some of the most startling reports coming in—eyewitness accounts of Ultra Beast sightings once more.
I’m desperate to know what’s going on, but given they’re not from this world, we should be cautious until we understand why this is happening.
Rhi and I will put our investigation hats on and learn what we can here. Would you head out into the field to gather info?
Rhi and I can confirm that the reports we’ve been getting are no mistake—we’ve got Ultra Beasts.
And that’s only accounting for the ones we know about. There might still be more out there.
What’s the meaning of all of this? Why are they back? Is our world in danger?
Their sudden appearance raises a lot of questions, but don’t worry. Rhi and I are committed to figuring out what’s causing this phenomenon.
Until we make more headway, please report anything else you find that might help our research. And be safe out there.
